title: Inside of East Austin Jiu-Jitsu Parlor ‚Äî one of the hidden gems of Austin, TXüî•
This Jiu-Jitsu Gym Brings East Austin Culture To Life | East Austin Jiu-Jitsu Parlor
description:
Austin, TX is known around the world as the mecca of professional jiu-jitsu. With elite teams like New Wave, B-Team, Six Blades, Fight Factory, and others calling the city home, it‚Äôs easy to focus solely on the top of the food chain.

But that‚Äôs just one part of the story.

In this episode, we shine a spotlight on East Austin Jiu-Jitsu Parlor ‚Äî a locally owned gym founded by longtime training partners who were part of the scene long before Austin became a jiu-jitsu hotspot. Their roots trace back to one of the city‚Äôs original gyms, East Austin Elite, and their mission today is to build something that blends the soul of Austin with the art of jiu-jitsu.

title: The American:  Rafael Lovato Jr (Ep 1) | Jiu-Jitsu Documentary
description:
Originally aired August 2016. Rafael Lovato Jr is a legend of the sport and the most decorated American competitor ever. World Champion, European Champion, Brazil National Absolute champion, you name it he‚Äôs won it. So how did a small town boy from Oklahoma become one of the most successful Brazilian jiu-jitsu champions ever? 

In Episode One of The American we bring you through the journey of Lovato Jr, from learning BJJ early on with his Dad, traveling to Brazil while he was just 16, and ultimately achieving his goals at the 2007 World Championships.

We‚Äôll also get a glimpse into Lovato‚Äôs training camp while he prepares for the Fight to Win Pro main event vs ‚ÄòCyborg‚Äô Abreu.

title: Defending The Crown: Andy Murasaki‚Äôs Journey to Greatness at Atos HQ
description:
Fresh off his 2024 triumph, Andy Murasaki returns to defend his title at The Crown 2025, one of the most prestigious events in Jiu-Jitsu.

Filmed at Atos HQ in San Diego, this episode takes you inside Andy‚Äôs world ‚Äî where discipline, precision, and daily grind shape a champion. Alongside insights from IBJJF Hall of Famer Andr√© Galv√£o, we follow Andy‚Äôs preparation, mindset, and evolution as he gets ready to face a new generation of hungry black belts in the middleweight division.

Watch as Andy reflects on:

-His intense training sessions at Atos HQ leading up to The Crown

-Learning from battles against world-class opponents like Pedro Maia and Jackson Nagai

-The lessons behind last year‚Äôs victory ‚Äî and his mission to win the right way this time

-How Atos‚Äô champion culture, led by Andr√© Galv√£o, continues to forge the next era of elite Jiu-Jitsu athletes

This is more than training ‚Äî it‚Äôs a look at what it takes to defend The Crown.

üì∫ Watch now and go behind the scenes with one of Jiu-Jitsu‚Äôs most technical and disciplined champions.

title: Rubens ‚ÄúCobrinha‚Äù Charles on Jalen ‚ÄúThe Future‚Äù Fonacier | IBJJF Talks
description:
In this episode of IBJJF Talks, Hall of Famer Rubens ‚ÄúCobrinha‚Äù Charles opens up about coaching one of Jiu-Jitsu‚Äôs brightest rising stars ‚Äî Jalen ‚ÄúThe Future‚Äù Fonacier ‚Äî to his first IBJJF World Championship at just 19 years old.

Cobrinha shares rare insight into Jalen‚Äôs journey from kid competitor to black belt champion, his unmatched discipline, and how he‚Äôs redefining what it means to be a modern athlete ‚Äî balancing academics and elite performance at the same time.

Watch as Cobrinha discusses:

-Jalen‚Äôs training camp and mindset leading up to Worlds

-How he ‚Äúbroke the rule‚Äù by proving you can succeed in both school and Jiu-Jitsu

-What sets Jalen apart as a once-in-a-generation competitor

-Lessons in discipline, resilience, and leadership that Cobrinha learned throughout his own Hall of Fame career

-The philosophy behind Alliance‚Äôs 15 World Team Titles and building champions for life

-Jalen‚Äôs story is more than just about winning gold ‚Äî it‚Äôs about focus, humility, and the mindset that defines true greatness.

üì∫ Watch now and hear how Rubens Cobrinha Charles is shaping the next era of Jiu-Jitsu champions.

At just 18 years old, Sarah Galv√£o has already built a r√©sum√© that most athletes can only dream of:

title: Jo√£o ‚ÄúBisnaga‚Äù Mendes: From Underdog to 2025 Featherweight World Champion | Full Interview
description:
From his first days on the mats in Brazil to standing atop the podium as the 2025 IBJJF Featherweight World Champion, Jo√£o ‚ÄúBisnaga‚Äù Mendes shares his inspiring journey.

In this exclusive 24-minute interview, Bisnaga opens up about:

How his father introduced him to Jiu-Jitsu and his early struggles competing against bigger, older athletes

The turning point of joining Atos HQ under Andr√© Galv√£o

Breakthrough moments at The Crown and against some of the toughest names in the featherweight division

Overcoming 7 years of challenges as a black belt before finally achieving his dream of becoming World Champion

What it means to win in one of the deepest and most unpredictable divisions in Jiu-Jitsu

Featherweight has crowned 9 different champions in the last 9 years, and in 2025, Jo√£o Mendes proved that persistence, belief, and relentless training can turn dreams into gold.

üì∫ Watch now and hear the story behind one of the most inspiring championship runs in IBJJF history.
